results.name: Silver Surfer
results.description: When Zenn-La was threatened by the world-devouring entity known as Galactus, Norrin Radd stood up for his home planet and offered to work for Galactus, finding him new planets to eat, in exchange for saving his own. Years later, the Surfer has protected Earth and many other planets, becoming one of the greatest heroes in the universe.

results.name: Skreet
results.description: The Proemial God Aegis revealed that Skreet was a Chaos Mite, a race of very small and powerful beings, which were deemed unstable by the Cosmic Consonance.

results.name: Stardust
results.description: As Herald for the world devourer, Galactus, Stardust found suitable worlds for her master to consume.

results.name: Super-Skrull
results.description: After the Fantastic Four stopped the Skrulls' attempted invasion of Earth, Skrull Emperor Dorrek invested vast resources into creating a superbeing of his own.

results.name: Talos
results.description: Born without the ability to shape shift like other Skrulls, Talos became a savage fighter and a decorated military commander.

results.name: Tenebrous
results.description: Tenebrous has existed in this universe since its infancy, and was imprisoned in the planet Kyln after a battle with Galactus.

results.name: Terrax
results.description: Tyros was once the dictator of the city Lanlak on the planet Birj, where his superhuman ability to command rocks and earth enabled him to overcome all resistance, but his rule of Lanlak came to an end when he was sought by the world-devouring Galactus to serve as his latest Herald.

results.name: Thanos
results.description: The Mad Titan Thanos, a melancholy, brooding individual, consumed with the concept of death, sought out personal power and increased strength, endowing himself with cybernetic implants until he became more powerful than any of his brethren.
